Assignment 1.02: Moving from Map to Map

This assignment builds on Assignment 1.01 by implementing a 401x401 world of maps centered at (0,0). The world is represented as a 2D array of pointers to singleMap structs. Maps are generated lazily using malloc only when first visited and are preserved for future revisits.

Movement commands include north (n), south (s), east (e), west (w), fly (f x y), and quit (q). Edge movement beyond the world boundary is prevented. Gates align correctly with previously generated neighboring maps, and maps on world borders do not generate outward-facing gates.

Building spawn probability declines linearly with Manhattan distance from the center, reaching a minimum of 5%. The center map (0,0) always contains both a Pokémart and Pokécenter.

Key Data Structures:
- singleMap *world[401][401]: Stores all generated maps.
- singleMap: Contains terrain and gate metadata.